div.div: Copilot Summary This pull request introduces several updates to the ALCF/helpers.sh and train_alcf.sh scripts, focusing on modularizing the code, improving environment setup, and enhancing debugging capabilities. Key changes include integrating the external ezpz utility, restructuring functions for better maintainability, and adding conditional debugging options. Modularization and External Utility Integration: Added sourcing of the external ezpz utility ( ezpz/bin/utils.sh ) to streamline job and environment setup in both ALCF/helpers.sh and train_alcf.sh . This replaces some existing setup logic with calls to ezpz functions. [1] [2] Function Restructuring: Refactored setup_run_cmd() by introducing a new helper function get_training_args() to encapsulate the logic for preparing training arguments, improving code clarity and maintainability. [1] [2] Debugging and Logging Enhancements: Added a conditional debugging block in train_aGPT() to enable detailed command tracing when the DEBUG environment variable is set. This aids in troubleshooting issues during training. Environment Variable Handling: Updated saveDSenv() to use default values ( :- ) for environment variables, ensuring robustness when certain variables are unset. Deprecated/Commented Code: Commented out legacy or deprecated code, including unused color definitions and environment variable setups for specific configurations (e.g., CCL variables for Aurora). These changes prepare the codebase for future updates. [1] [2]
